        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 5:59PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 559 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Aldape Summit, or 10 miles east of Boise, moving northwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Aldape Summit and Lucky Peak Reservoir around 600 PM MDT.
Bogus Basin Ski Area around 610 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
